    public A() {
        this.b = new B(this);
    }

This of course assumes your class B has a constructor which accepts an `A`, e.g., 
   
    public B(A a) {
        this.a = a;
    }

`B` needs an explicit reference to its owner:

    public class B {
      private final A owner;

      public B(A owner) {
        this.owner = owner;
      }

      public A getOwner() {
        return owner;
      }
    }

And in `A`:

    public A() {
      b = new B(this);
